he first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]},{"name":"Isobel","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Isabel ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Isabell was born in 1315, in Worcester, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom. She married John de Washborne in 1328, in Worcester, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1370, at the age of 55."},"et":{"1315–1370":"1315–1370","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","1310–1358":"1310–1358","1332–1360":"1332–1360","1350–1406":"1350–1406","1350–1423":"1350–1423","1315":"1315","1358":"1358","1423":"1423","1332":"1332","1310":"1310","1350":"1350","1360":"1360","1370":"1370","about 1350":"umbes 1350","1406":"1406","1328":"1328","Little Washbourne, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Little Washbourne, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Worcester, Worcestershire, England":"Worcester, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Snodhill, Herefordshire, England":"Snodhill, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stanford, Worcestershirer, England":"Stanford, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Overbury, Wychavon District, Worcestershire, England":"Overbury, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Worcester, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Worcester, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1315–1370":"1315–1370","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","1310–1358":"1310–1358","1332–1360":"1332–1360","1350–1406":"1350–1406","1350–1423":"1350–1423","1315":"1315","1358":"1358","1423":"1423","1332":"1332","1310":"1310","1350":"1350","1360":"1360","1370":"